<DOCTYPE> MISCELLANEOUS TEXT (slug-filter) </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-10 15:29 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A3241 &Cx1f; tad-z
u s &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-BKN-EASTNOTES11-COX     04-10 0523
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BKN-EASTNOTES11-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Heat ends slump in emphatic fashion
 &HT;    By Jeffrey Denberg
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ After losing six of seven _ the team's worst slump
since Pat Riley's first year (1995-96) _ the Heat recovered to
knock off three titans _ Washington, Toronto and Dallas.
</P>
<P>
   The Raptors shot .296 in a 92-70 rout at Air Canada Centre. ``To
make a team quit like that _ it makes you feel good,'' Heat forward
P.J. Brown said. ``Vince Carter (3-for-10, 12 points) was down
tonight. He basically said, `I quit. It's too hard.'''
</P>
<P>
   OK, but Riley, unhappy with everyone except Alonzo Mourning
during the skid, refuses to acknowledge his team is out of its
slump because he doesn't want complacency, especially with Miami
chasing the Magic in the Atlantic.
</P>
<P>
   Stealing steals lead
</P>
<P>
   Now Mookie Blaylock knows what he has to do to win another
steals title. Kendall Gill used 11 steals against the Heat (tying
an NBA record set by San Antonio's Larry Kenon in 1976), seven
against the Celtics and five more against the Wizards to go from
11th in the league to first with 2.44.
</P>
<P>
   Plain speaking
</P>
<P>
   Talking: The Bulls got waxed by 32 by the Pistons last week and
late in the game Dickey Simpkins started something when he took
down Pistons forward Grant Hill. ``All night they're taking it to
the rack. Someone had to let them know, `Hey, you can't come in
here.''' Simpkins said. ``That's part of this game, hard fouls. I
guess they made more of it because he's the great, all-American
boy. That's cool. I just wanted to let people know you can't dunk
on us and take it to the rack on us.'' Pacers give up on McKey
</P>
<P>
   A sore point around the Pacers _ literally _ has been the knee
of Derrick McKey, who has been out all season. But coach Larry Bird
said the team won't wait much longer for McKey. ``If he's not back
in the next few days, we might as well call it a season for him,''
Bird said. ``These guys who went through this tough season, to
bring another guy into the mix can hurt you. Everybody's
disappointed. But if the man's hurt, he's hurt. We need him, but
there comes a time of the season when you've got to make a decision
whether he should come back or not.''
</P>
<P>
   Dumars milestone
</P>
<P>
   Joe Dumars played in his 1,000th game, becoming the 56th to do
it, the 10th with one team and the eighth to do it with his first
team. The other eight: Hal Greer, Dolph Schayes, Hakeem Olajuwon,
Karl Malone, John Stockton, Calvin Murphy and John Havlicek.
</P>
<P>
   Game operations crews fined
</P>
<P>
   The NBA finally took action to rein in the game operations crews
that run rampant league-wide. The Raptors' bunch game drew a quiet
$10,000 slap for actions in a game against the Knicks on March 21.
When former Raptor Marcus Camby entered the game, the PA system
played the sound of a baby crying. Also, when guard Latrell
Sprewell was at the free-throw line, the stadium scoreboards
flashed the word ``choke,'' referring to Sprewell's infamous
altercation with Golden State coach P.J. Carlesimo a year ago.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
