   OUTDOORS
</P>
<P>
   FISHING-WOMEN _ Fishing against the good ol' boys has never
dissuaded Pam Martin of Bainbridge nor the handful of other women
anglers who've tried to follow the footsteps of former Bass 'n Gal
champion Voja Reed, the first woman to enter a major men's
tournament when she competed in a BASSMASTER event in 1991. Martin
has the determination _ as well as the skill _ to excel in the
male-dominated sport. (Bernarde, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 20.
