   TAX-BURDEN _ WASHINGTON _ The federal taxes paid are the highest
percentage of the nation's output of any peacetime in history. Are
American households feeling a bigger pinch as they mail in their
tax returns this month? Story will examine the total burden of
taxes, said to be 40 percent, and how they affect various income
groups. Which taxes are growing? Which ones are hidden? What
changes are in the works in Congress that could change the burden?
(Malone, Cox News Service). MOVED THURSDAY.
