KEATING _ In an agreement with federal prosecu tors, Charles H
Keating Jr. acknowledged concocting phony loans to siphon $975,000
out of American Continental Corporation, the Phoenix-based
corporation where he was CEO. With that plea bargain, Keating
shattered his own myth, the long-running legend of himself as a
high-flying financiavisionary, bold entrepreneur and
</P>
