to the polls in a little more than five weeks to answer the $1.8
billion question: Hitch or ditch? Will the East Valley hitch its
economic and cultural wagon to the massive Rio Salado Crossing
convention center and football stadium, or ditch the notion of
spending tax money for a profes sional sports and convention
complex? By ROBBIE SHERWOOD. Story will move in the ``A''
category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
HOCKEY-ARENA _ It appeared at first that opponents of a Phoenix
