r s &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-FBC-USC-LADN-(SLANG)     04-10 0407
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FBC-USC-LADN-(SLANG) </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
POLLRD LIKELY OUT FOR SEASON
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By SCOTT WOLF  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   &LR; LOS ANGELES _ USC's spring scrimmage Saturday was dampened by
the news that sophomore middle linebacker Mike Pollard tore knee
ligaments two days earlier and is likely lost for the season.
</P>
<P>
   An official announcement from the university is pending, but
Pollard apparently injured his knee during Thursday's practice.
</P>
<P>
   ``It doesn't look good,'' USC coach Paul Hackett said.
</P>
<P>
   Without Pollard, junior Zeke Moreno becomes the full-time
starting middle linebacker. There had been some thought to letting
Pollard start in the middle, with Moreno staying outside. Moreno
missed the scrimmage to be in a wedding.
</P>
<P>
   Other than Pollard's injury, there were some encouraging signs
during Saturday's 56-play scrimmage at Howard Jones Field.
</P>
<P>
   Notably, sophomore tailback Sultan McCullough seems light years
ahead of last season and ready to challenge Chad Morton for playing
time. McCullough gained 99 yards in 13 carries with a long run of
21 yards, and scored on a 10-yard run. He also had a fumble.
</P>
<P>
   ``The running was particularly good,'' Hackett said.
``Particularly (McCullough). Last fall, like most freshmen, you're
not sure what to do. He's working his way through things. He's
developing.''
</P>
<P>
   With Hackett hoping to use more split-back formations,
McCullough could potentially line up aside Morton in the backfield.
</P>
<P>
   The other player to emerge was senior wide receiver Windrell
Hayes, who will start opposite R. Jay Soward. Hayes had five
receptions for 113 yards. Soward caught a 39-yard touchdown pass.
</P>
<P>
   Quarterbacks Carson Palmer and Mike Van Raaphorst were both
solid. Palmer completed 7 of 11 passes for 138 yards and one
touchdown; Van Raaphorst was 5 of 6 for 77 yards.
</P>
<P>
   If the offense had a weak spot, it was the offensive line, which
had several false-start penalties. There were 16 penalties, with
six on offense and 10 by the defense.
</P>
<P>
   ``We lost our poise far too many times,'' Hackett said. ``There
were far too many penalties. Other than that, I was delighted.''
</P>
<P>
   Free safety Darnell Lacy led the defense with six tackles.
Converted quarterback John Fox had five tackles in his first game
at linebacker. Defensive end Lonnie Ford had two sacks.
</P>
<P>
   USC continues spring practice through April 23. Practices are
open to the public.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-04-10-99 2221EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
